			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Ok, from what I've read, we're going to get even more travel options wity LDoN.  Now, from certain places, we can just /say &lt;zonename&gt; and bam, we're there.  I'm not sure of details, so maybe the LDoN travel isn't going to make things much worse, but consider this:
<br />

<br />
Been to any of our major cities on Norrath lately (besides PoK and Shadowhaven)?  They are completely empty.  I don't know how you all feel about this, but I think it takes a huge amount of character and believability out of the game.
<br />

<br />
I remember (with great fondness) sitting in Freeport, Qeynos and other cities and watching the hustle and the bustle.
<br />

<br />
PoK makes any other city nearly obsolete from the standpoint of quick and easy, which is all many, many EQ gamers care about anymore.  Personally, I like the idea of people knowing their home city best, as well as some aligned ports.
<br />

<br />
Add to this, that the stones in PoK make it possible to get nearly everywhere without knowing a stitch of Norrathian geography.  There are a whole batch of players now that know Norrath only by the stones there.
<br />

<br />
Also note, the ethnicity that distance brought to places like Everfrost is gone.  Instaports means everywhere on Norrath is equally populated by all races.  No more is it a shock to see outsiders in certain areas.
<br />

<br />
Expansions add travel, items, and ease of use for the non-roleplayer.  They do nothing but degrade, destroy and squander the personality of Norrath, its cities and the flavor of a real-feeling alternate reality.  Now, with LDoN, even items lose their personality.
<br />

<br />
I loved EQ in the early days, as it was a haven.  A long time pen and paper role players dream.  A living, breathing world that felt real, had personality, ethnicity in its cities, geography, boats, and was a joy to spend time in.  Now, we have none of this, but we can get everything and everywhere fast and easy.  Isn't it amazing what money can do?<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://home.rochester.rr.com/drool/whiskerlings.jpg" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
