			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The problem is alot of the traveling is exactly what it is, a useless timesink made more frustrating by its bugginess.
<br />

<br />
For instance, i was attempting to take the shuttles to TD yesterday.
<br />

<br />
Get on a shuttle and wait 20 minutes.
<br />

<br />
Shuttle takes off but "shoves" me off into the water as it zones into TD.  So i didnt zone with it.  
<br />

<br />
Swim back to dock in BB, await shuttles to come back.
<br />

<br />
20 minutes later shuttles are back.  I get on one.
<br />

<br />
20 minutes later the shuttle leaves again. (keep in mind i have already spent an hour trying to get to TD)
<br />

<br />
This time, the shuttle does zone me into TD, but upon zone in a shuttle moving in the opposite direction slides "through" my shuttle and i am transfered onto that shuttle and zoned back into BB. 
<br />

<br />
gave up after that.
<br />

<br />
Whens the last time a bus IRL "shoved" you off before your stop? Whens the last time another bus "passed through" your bus and transfered you to the other bus in the process?
<br />

<br />
Some things were great ideas in the game, but if not implemented properly become nothing but useless timesinks.  I do agree pok ports broke everything though.<br />_________________<br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Elder Jowaa Emanon</span>
<br />
Ninja Kat of Vallon
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Jowaa</span>
