			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">When I first installed Everquest, I done so accepting I was about to enter a 'world'.
<br />

<br />
This world was fraught with dangers. You can get jumped by god knows what just trying to get to your friends. When you're a lv10 Druid (as I was) this was scarey. This was exciting ! Will I make it ? 
<br />

<br />
The unknown is what motivated me. I couldn't wait to get 14, sow, and I was gonna explore ! No clicky ports, no maps saying 'Go here, do this, congrats another ding' - just my nerves of steel and the sense of the unknown driving me on. And my 'gate' finger itching nervously...
<br />

<br />
Newbies miss out on this. There is no longer a 'world' - it's just a bunch of zones connected by insta port stones. All you need do is level up. Then it's off to the next stone. Grats on 65, btw !
<br />

<br />
I look back now. I'm GLAD travel was hard. I'll never forget my first boat trip. I learned the lay of the land. I found out which zone goes to where. But most importantly of all, I can take you and show you. The first time I ever experienced a port was when I got my own port spells. Oh boy, did I earn them too. And it just made getting them a sweeter experience. 
<br />

<br />
I left GFay/BB at the tender age of 14. Most now will leave at 9, PoP stone it to Shadeweavers and head for Paludal. A few days later and their 25, learning precious little about how to play their class. Wonder why there are so many idiots about ? Because EQ is TOO EASY. It caters for the lazy - the 'I want it all NOW' crowd.
<br />

<br />
Sure, travelling is a pain in the butt when you've a long way to go. But nobody told me EQ was going to be quick and easy. I had Quake for quick and easy. EQ was my little bit of heaven that I got lost in for hours on end.
<br />

<br />
I signed up knowing it would be a long voyage. I accepted that fact wholeheartedly. No, I positively WANTED that.
<br />

<br />
But what do I care ? I've done my adventuring. I've had all the thrills'n'spills that go with it. I'm assuming the newbies want an 'easy' life. That's fair enough. 
<br />

<br />
They've missed out on a lot.
<br />

<br />
I've ranted a bit in there, so apologies in advance  <img src="images/smiles/icon_redface.gif" alt="Embarassed" border="0" /><br />_________________<br />Tilond - Elvaan Monk saving the world on Vana'diel.
<br />

<br />
(Can save Norrath too for a fee)</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
