				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I started EQ about 6 months after it was released. I came to EQ from Ultima Online. I was still playing UO while playing EQ. I loved my castle to much to leave. One of the first things I hated was the travel time. I would spend hours a night just running from Qyenos to NK for a CR. Then later hours on boats to and from Kunark. I stayed about 3 months and left EQ for UO. But, there was no high end UO and I had done it all. 
<br />

<br />
So I came back to EQ but this time as a druid. EQ was a wonderful game after that. I even stopped playing my druid at all even for ports after PoP came out. My cleric could get to just about anywhere in the game in 2 -3 zones.
<br />

<br />
As for citys I only goto the ones i should be going to. I spend alot of time in Freeport and Qyenos (human cleric). I still do tradeskills in my human cities and offer advice/help/buffs/gear to low level players. I hated being new in EQ so I like to make some armor, weapons, and jewlery to the newbies. Why do I need to goto any other cities in the old world?
<br />

<br />
Ya, just like all of us old time players. I have a great many old fart "I walked 10 miles up hill in a snowstorm to get to scholl barefoot" stories. But, in the end it was a HUGE waste of time. Heck ni the amount of travel time I have back in the day I could easily get an extra AA a day with that time. I could get 5 AA for an old fassion true CR hassle.
<br />

<br />
Hell get ride of all stones/portals/books and goto the UO method of runes/recalls/gates. Then we can go anywhere we want any time. hehe then we have a new method of getting even with players. Although I bet in EQ you would lose your account. Use to love opening gates for beggers for ports to a small 2 foot island in the middle of the ocean and then ignoring them.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=88038">Sycloness</a> 
