			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><span style="color: darkblue">I am of two minds on this issue. I remember fondly the days of hunting outside Freeport, walking tentatively thru new and dangerous areas. There was more of a sence of community, and more of a sence of region. I didnt'  see an Ogre (other than a merchant) until I was Level 10, which took more like 3 month's rather than todays 3 hours. 
<br />

<br />
But I also had limited time to spend playing (still do). I never know how long I can play, and I may have to log at a moments notice. So I almost always SOLO. In the old days, soloing was the absolute SLOWEST way to gain levels. Without the ability to travel quickly, I was limited to a few zones, cause I couldn't spend the time traveling. I got frustrated, and decided I just didn't have the time to play this game. I loved it, but just couldn't devote the time. 
<br />

<br />
Now I pop from here to there in a flash. But this DOES detract from the game. I recently started a new Troll BL on Stromm. I hunted for a short while in my home zone, but mobs were hard to come by, and there were too many ppl around. POP, I'm in Shadeweavers. Kill a few hoppers, kill about 10 lesser shades. I collected 2 Swirling Shadows, 3 Low Quality Rockhopper Hides, 2 Medium Quality Hides. POP, in the Bazzar, 5 minutes and I have 30pp to spend. So at level 4 I have a PSU, Greyhopper Hide Tunic, Wodden Shield, and no reason to return to my home or do any of the armour or weapon quests there. By Level 6 I have STAT enhancing earings and rings. LEVEL 6! This is not good. 
<br />

<br />
I think that the PoK books should have a Level Limit. Or a component that is only acheivable with a higher level. Keep players in their home territory untill Level 20 or so. This will get the newbie areas outside of PC to be used more. And the EXP bonus in PC has got to be nerfed, or similar areas added to all the other home areas. It just dosn't pay to play anywhere else. Shadeweavers has the best and easiest obtainable loot (Swirling Shadows, Chunk of Condensed Shadows), and the Best EXP area right next to it. Why would you Play elsewhere?
<br />

<br />
Unfortunatly, I don't see these issues being addressed. The market for this kind of game is increasingly going to the younger player, who wants everything at once. Many games have cheats published before the game is even released, so the player has GOD mode, Unlimited Lives, and Unlimited Ammo, from the very start, and SOE is trying to recreate EQ in that image. The sad part is, compared to other games out there, EQ does take longer to level, and more roleplaying. How far this will go we can only see. i think I may switch to the RP server, just for variety. </span><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=788411" target="_blank" class="postlink">Kunnar Dar'Tigris</a>, 30th Vah Shir and his companion Buffy the Vampire Slayer (Vazelle)
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=861809" target="_blank" class="postlink">Kracke</a>, 25th Troll, and his eternally hungry companion, Gronk (Firona Vie) 
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">Call Gronk Insurance, for all your Insurance needs. Life, Health, Personal Property, and Warder Repop Insurance available. 
<br />
The Official Insurance of Legacy of Sha.</span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
