				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">When I started playing, about a month before Luclin, the traveling was a big part of the game. It was a part that really made the world HUGE, awe inspiring, rich and it was one of the parts that that made me fall in love with EQ.. 
<br />

<br />
Now its no longer a part of the game, its more a obstacle to get over then an ejoyable experience. Well, my veiws may be baised since I have played a wizard up to lvl 65. But STILL, even though I could port and didnt have to run everywhere I cant find ONE zone (that I have access too that is..) that I can't find my way in. It was FUN to travel around on foot to see the world, but that dont seem to be the veiws of newer players. Its all about leveling up asap, get in a rading guild, get ph4t l33wts and then dont really do anything else but to sit in the same, g'damn boring place, hour after hour and kill the same type of mobs over and over again. Wheres the fun in that?
<br />

<br />
It would be fun to do an experiment some day, port all people in PoK during prime time to some remote place like Lavastorm. Tell them to run to Lake Rathear (sp? <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="Razz" border="0" />) without the use of PoK books, wayfarer camps or ports. Anyone have a guess of how many percent would make it without getting lost? <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="Wink" border="0" /><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=720122" target="_blank"> Evandar </a>
<br />
Proud memeber of <a href="http://www.istid.se" target="_blank"> &lt;Istid&gt; </a>
<br />
Antonius Bayle</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
