				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">travel time is nice... but not when its unnessicary.
<br />

<br />
No-one would complain if it was actually ALWAYS fun to make those long runs. See im one of those people everyone says EQ is dumbed down for.
<br />

<br />
Ive been playing since beta. But i dont have the time and will power to camp for items exp... EVER. If something is boring, i dont do it.
<br />

<br />
Hard... and boring do NOT go hand in hand my friends.
<br />

<br />
Thats the problem. EQ at the begining made things hard.. because they were so boring. Can you honestly say the 10th time you ran from Qeynos to Freeport was still FUN?? Hell no... it was a HUGE chunck of time that was just another boring run. If you actually thought it was fun everytime you did the run... man youd be a great accountant. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />
<br />

<br />

<br />
I agree its alittle to easy now, but be honest there are few "new" players to EQ now adays. Mostly its people coming back from time to time, or dedicated people making new and insteresting ALTs. 
<br />

<br />
I seriously doubt SOE changed the game to make it easier for new players (some yes like the instant spells and gear), but rather did it so the currect list of players didnt get sick of creating new characters. 
<br />

<br />
About the 5th time creating a new character in the old world most people would get so fed up with the treadmill they would leave comepletly. Hell i know many people who gave up after their 1st character.
<br />

<br />
not because it was "hard" but because once youve been scared by a giant and learn how to avoid them... they are just another obsticle and a waste of your time.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=421281" target="_blank" class="postlink">Crankie</a> - 52nd Troll Primalist of Innoruuk - Veeshan Server
<br />

<br />
Tiggro - Black Panther and dreamer of FV
<br />

<br />
Ohh yeeeaahhh small is good! 
<br />
