			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The "fun" in having to run, was the results this caused.  Areas that were "ethnic"... other players understanding the zones better...., etc.
<br />

<br />
Sometimes some benefits occur because of difficulty, just like real life.  I loved that fact that noone went to Everfrost.  It meant a very cultural/local feeling there when I went home as my barbarian.  Then, they added the surefall glade port, and PoK, and its a friggin zoo.
<br />

<br />
I guess what I'm saying is that part of the "fun" from the old days, was the effect that travel had, rather than the actual travel.
<br />

<br />
My biggest pleasure from EQ came from how real it felt as a world sometimes.  Now, it just feels like a game, where you click on various dungeons and there you are.  If I wanted that, I'd buy doom.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
